## **Navigation model**

| **Layer** | **Implementation** | **Screens** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Root Stack** | Expo Router Stack — no header | auth group, onboarding group, tabs group |
| **Auth group** | Stack within (auth) — no header | sign-in, sign-up, forgot-password |
| **Onboarding group** | Stack within (onboarding) — full screen, no tab bar, progress bar component | ob-00 through ob-08b (10 screens) |
| **Tab bar** | Expo Router Tabs — 5 tabs, persistent, cream background on screen | home, week, search, mymeals, profile |
| **Home stack** | Stack within (tabs)/home — slides right for detail screens | H-01 (Day View) → H-02 (Meal Detail) |
| **Modals** | Bottom sheet via @gorhom/bottom-sheet — not stack navigation | H-06 Not Today, H-07 Never, H-08 Add to date, S-03 Filter panel |
| **Deep links** | foofoo:// scheme. Expo Router handles automatic deep link routing from push notifications | foofoo://home, foofoo://meal/{id}, foofoo://mymeals, foofoo://profile/never |

## **State management layers**

| **Layer** | **Library** | **What it owns** | **Why this library** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Server state** | TanStack Query v5 | API responses: daily plan, week plan, dish detail, search results, user profile. Auto-caching, background refresh, stale-while-revalidate. | Handles caching, deduplication, offline fallback, and background sync automatically. Best-in-class for async server data. |
| **Offline persistence** | TanStack Query + MMKV persister | Today's plan persisted across app restarts. Dish data cached for 24 hours. User profile cached indefinitely. | MMKV is 10× faster than AsyncStorage. Synchronous reads mean the cached plan appears instantly on offline open with zero flicker. |
| **Client UI state** | Zustand v4 | Locked slots map, swipe-reveal open state, active modal, gesture in progress, offline banner visibility. | Minimal boilerplate. Synchronous updates match gesture animation speed. No provider needed. |
| **Auth session** | Supabase Auth + Zustand | JWT token, user ID, session expiry. Stored in SecureStore on device. | SecureStore is encrypted. Supabase handles refresh automatically. Zustand exposes session to components without Provider. |
| **Event queue** | MMKV (raw key-value) | Interaction events queued when offline. Format: array of serialised REEvent objects. | Events must survive app restart if offline. MMKV persists synchronously. Queue flushed on NetInfo reconnect event. |

## **Gesture system — implementation**

| **Gesture** | **Implementation** | **Thread** | **Performance spec** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Swipe carousel on meal card (left/right)** | PanGestureHandler wrapping card. On x-displacement > 40px: trigger carousel open via Zustand. Card translates with gesture using Animated.Value driven by Reanimated. | UI thread (Reanimated worklet) | < 100ms visual response. Tested on Pixel 3a (lowest target device). |
| **Swipe-reveal action buttons (left swipe)** | PanGestureHandler. On x-displacement > 40px left: card translates left 80px, buttons enter from right. Distinct from carousel — different threshold and direction. | UI thread | < 100ms. Release snaps back if < 80px. Release past 80px reveals buttons. |
| **Lock icon tap** | TouchableOpacity with haptic feedback (Haptics.impactAsync). Zustand updates locked_slots map synchronously. | JS thread (fast enough for tap) | < 16ms state update. Haptic fires on same frame. |
| **Swap icon tap** | TouchableOpacity. Triggers TanStack Query fetch for alternative dishes (pre-fetched on plan load). Opens carousel. | JS thread | Alternatives pre-fetched — carousel opens with data immediately. |
| **Pull-to-refresh on Day View** | RefreshControl on ScrollView. Calls TanStack Query refetch() for unlocked slots only. Locked slots excluded from refetch. | JS thread | System pull-to-refresh animation. RE call < 3s. |
| **OB-07 dish preference swipe** | PanGestureHandler. RIGHT (+x) = YES, LEFT (–x) = NOPE. Stamp overlay fades in as card moves. Visible buttons (heart/X) trigger same logic without gesture. | UI thread | Spring animation. Card flies off over 260ms. |

# **05  Backend architecture — Supabase**

## **Project configuration**

| **Setting** | **Value** | **Notes** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Region** | ap-south-1 (Mumbai) | Closest AWS region to Indian users. Reduces API latency by 40–80ms vs Singapore. |
| **PostgreSQL version** | 15 | Supports Row Level Security, generated columns, GIN indexes for full-text search. |
| **Auth providers (MVP)** | Email + password | Social login (Google, Apple) added in Phase 0.5 per F-51. |
| **Auth providers (Phase 0.5+)** | Email + Google + Apple | Google: OAuth 2.0. Apple: Sign in with Apple (required for iOS if other social login exists). |
| **Row Level Security** | Enabled on ALL tables | No exceptions. Every table has at least one policy. Service role bypasses RLS in Edge Functions only. |
| **Database schemas** | public (app data), re_engine (RE data) | Schema separation enforces RE isolation. App never directly queries re_engine tables. |
| **Storage buckets** | dish-photos (public read, no user write) | Dish photos uploaded by admin only. Public CDN URL. No user-uploaded content in MVP. |
| **Realtime** | Disabled in MVP | Not required until social features (Phase 3). Saves Realtime connection quota. |
| **Connection pooling** | PgBouncer (Supabase built-in) | Required when Edge Functions scale. Prevents connection exhaustion under concurrent requests. |
| **Environment** | Production: foofoo-mvp project. Staging: foofoo-staging project. | Separate Supabase projects for prod and staging. Same schema. Secrets managed via EAS environment variables. |

## **Edge Functions — the five endpoints**

| **Endpoint** | **Method** | **Runtime** | **Responsibility** | **Auth** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **POST /v1/recommendations** | POST | Deno (TypeScript) | Full RE pipeline: validate → assign_persona → generate_class_plan → generate_addons → expand_dishes → score_candidates → mmr_rerank → safety_gate → return slate. Writes to plan_cache. | JWT (service role internally; validates user JWT on entry) |
| **POST /v1/events** | POST | Deno | Receives user interaction event (dish_accepted, dish_never, dish_not_today, dish_swiped_past, dish_cooked, dish_ordered, dish_rated, plan_opened, session_depth). Writes to suggestion_logs. Triggers async feature store update. | JWT — anon key allowed; RLS validates user_id matches auth.uid() |
| **POST /v1/onboarding** | POST | Deno | Processes completed onboarding object. Calls assign_persona(). Returns initial persona_assignment + confidence_score. Writes to profiles table. | JWT |
| **GET /v1/plan/{user_id}/{week}** | GET | Deno | Returns cached 7-day class plan for a user-week from plan_cache. Falls back to generating if cache miss. | JWT — user can only fetch own plan (RLS) |
| **GET /v1/health** | GET | Deno | Returns RE health status: database connection, last successful plan generation timestamp, current re_version. Used by app to decide whether to show cached plan. | None — public endpoint |

## **RE pipeline — step-by-step implementation**

| **Stage** | **Function** | **Input** | **Output** | **Failure behaviour** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **1. Validate** | validateRequest() | User JWT, meal_slot, date, context | Validated user_id, IST date, context object | Return 400. App falls back to cached plan. |
| **2. Assign persona** | assignPersona() | user_id | persona_id, confidence_score from re_engine.cohort_matrix + profiles | If no persona match: use MC_GENERIC fallback with confidence 0.35 |
| **3. Generate class plan** | generateClassPlan() | persona_id, day_of_week, day_type (weekday/weekend) | Array of class_codes for each meal slot: [{slot:'breakfast', class_code:'BF_LIGHT_GRAIN'}] | Use default class plan for cohort if DB read fails |
| **4. Generate add-ons** | generateAddons() | member_segments[], class plan | addon_slots[]: [{member_name, slot, addon_class_code}] | Skip add-ons. Primary plan returned without add-ons. |
| **5. Expand to dishes** | expandClassToDishes() | class_code, user hard constraints (diet, allergens, never_list) | candidate_dishes[]: dish_ids that pass ALL hard constraints | If < 3 candidates after constraint filter: widen class, log as coverage gap |
| **6. Score candidates** | scoreCandidates() | candidate_dishes, user_id, context, confidence_score | scored_dishes[]: [{dish_id, score: float}] using weighted formula | If scoring fails: rank by cohort popularity (fallback signal) |
| **7. MMR re-rank** | mmrRerank() | scored_dishes, already_selected dishes for this plan | reranked_dishes[]: diversity-balanced slate | If < 8 dishes after MMR: pad with highest-scoring remaining candidates |
| **8. Safety gate** | safetyGateCheck() | final slate, user constraints | PASS or FAIL with violation details | FAIL: discard slate, regenerate (max 2 retries). After 2 failures: return 500 with cached plan fallback signal |
| **9. Return** | buildResponse() | Validated final slate | JSON response per RE-DOC-01 contract | — |

## **Database schema — overview (detail in DOC-11)**

| **Schema** | **Table group** | **Tables** | **Accessed by** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **public** | User data | profiles, household_members, onboarding_sessions | App client (anon key + RLS), Edge Functions |
| **public** | Content (read-only for users) | dishes, ingredients, dish_ingredients, meal_classes | App client (anon key), Edge Functions |
| **public** | Plan state | week_plans, plan_slots, suggestion_logs, plan_cache | Edge Functions write. App client reads (own rows only). |
| **public** | Events | interaction_events, push_notification_logs | Edge Functions write. Never readable by client. |
| **re_engine** | RE data | cohort_matrix, re_class_taxonomy, re_dish_genome, re_persona_slot_plan, re_segment_addon_rule, re_state_class_affinity | Edge Functions only. App client has no access. |
| **re_engine** | Feature store | user_taste_vectors, class_affinity_weights, never_list_cache | Edge Functions read/write only. |

## **Cron jobs**

| **Job** | **Schedule (UTC)** | **IST equivalent** | **Action** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Morning plan pre-generation** | 23:30 UTC | 05:00 IST | Generates plans for all users active in last 7 days. Populates plan_cache. Queues OneSignal push notifications per user's configured time. |
| **Cohort weight recalibration** | Sunday 18:00 UTC | Sunday 23:30 IST | Compares actual acceptance rates per cohort vs research weights. Updates cohort_matrix.weight where reality diverges. Runs on acceptance data from past 7 days. |
| **Feature store cleanup** | Daily 00:00 UTC | 05:30 IST | Removes interaction events older than 2 years (DPDP Act retention policy). Purges deleted user data. |
| **RE health check** | Every 5 minutes | Continuous | Calls GET /v1/health. Alerts if health check fails 3 consecutive times. |

# **06  Security architecture**

## **Authentication and authorisation**

| **Component** | **Implementation** | **Why** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **User authentication** | Supabase Auth. Email + password MVP. JWT issued on sign-in. Stored in SecureStore (encrypted, device keychain). | SecureStore uses device's secure enclave. Tokens never in AsyncStorage (unencrypted). |
| **API authorisation** | Every Supabase API call includes Authorization: Bearer {jwt} header. Supabase validates JWT and passes auth.uid() to RLS policies. | Zero-trust: every request is validated. No session cookies. Stateless. |
| **Row Level Security** | Every table has RLS enabled and at least one policy. Example: users can only read/write rows where user_id = auth.uid(). | A compromised anon key cannot read another user's data. RLS is enforced at the database layer — cannot be bypassed by client code. |
| **Service role key** | Only used inside Supabase Edge Functions (server-side). Never in React Native app code. Never in git. | Service role bypasses RLS — it can read all rows. Must never be exposed to client. |
| **RE schema access** | re_engine schema has no RLS policies readable by the anon key. App client has zero access to RE tables. | Prevents reverse-engineering of the RE algorithm. Users cannot read cohort weights or scoring formulas. |
| **Secrets management** | All secrets in environment variables: .env.local (local dev, gitignored) and EAS Secrets (production builds). Zero hardcoded values in source code. | Automated secret scan in GitHub Actions CI blocks any commit containing key patterns. |

## **DPDP Act 2023 compliance — technical implementation**

| **Requirement** | **Technical implementation** | **Verified by** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Granular consent at signup** | Consent captured per data category in onboarding. Stored in profiles.consent_record (JSONB). Timestamp + version recorded. | Legal audit before launch |
| **Data export within 72 hours** | Edge Function: GET /v1/user/export — returns all user data as JSON. Triggered by user from P-08 screen. Queued job completes within 72 hours. | Tested: request → delivery time |
| **Account deletion within 72 hours** | Edge Function: DELETE /v1/user — soft-deletes all rows (sets deleted_at). Cron job permanently purges within 72 hours. | Tested: deletion request → zero rows verifiable by user |
| **Interaction event retention** | All interaction_events older than 2 years purged by daily cron. Policy documented in Privacy Policy. | Monthly audit log |
| **Age gate** | OB-03 or signup includes age verification. Users under 13 blocked per DPDP minor protection provisions. | QA test case: under-13 input blocked |
| **Data minimisation** | Only fields that materially change the meal plan are collected in onboarding. Validated against DOC-04 NFR. | Schema audit: every column must have a documented RE impact reason |

# **07  Performance architecture**

| **NFR** | **Target** | **Implementation** | **Measured by** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Plan generation speed** | < 3s end-to-end on budget Android | Plan pre-generated by morning cron at 5 AM IST. App reads from plan_cache on open — a single DB read, not a full RE pipeline call. | Sentry performance monitoring: trace from app open to plan render |
| **On-demand plan generation** | < 3s when cache is cold (new user) | RE pipeline optimised: indexed cohort_matrix queries, pre-computed class-to-dish maps. Edge Function: < 800ms. Network round trip: < 200ms. Render: < 500ms. | Load test before launch on Pixel 3a (reference device) |
| **Swipe carousel latency** | < 100ms visual response | Reanimated v3 runs animations on UI thread. Gesture handler detects displacement on UI thread. No JS thread involvement during swipe. | Frame profiler: every gesture interaction |
| **Search result latency** | < 500ms | Full-text search using PostgreSQL GIN index on dishes.search_vector (tsvector of name + cuisine + class tags). Supabase RPC function: < 200ms query time. | PostHog: search_result_time event |
| **App cold start** | < 2s | Hermes JS engine (faster startup). MMKV synchronous read of cached plan before first network request. Skeleton loaders shown immediately. | Sentry: app_start span |
| **Image loading** | < 500ms per dish photo | Cloudinary CDN: 800×600 WebP. expo-image: disk cache first, memory cache second. Blurhash placeholder during load (zero blank space). | PostHog: image_load_time event |
| **Offline plan display** | Instant (< 100ms) | MMKV persister on TanStack Query: today's plan read synchronously from disk. No network call needed for render. | Manual test: aeroplane mode, restart app |
| **60fps gesture animations** | Sustained 60fps during swipe | Reanimated v3 worklets run on UI thread. No JS thread bridge calls during animation. Tested on Pixel 3a. | Frame profiler: 0 dropped frames on swipe |

## **Reference test device**

| **Minimum specification for performance testing: **Pixel 3a (2019) with 4GB RAM, Snapdragon 670, Android 12. Every performance target must be met on this device. Testing only on flagship devices is not acceptable — 60%+ of Foofoo's target users are on mid-range Android devices. |
| --- |

# **08  Offline architecture**

Foofoo must be useful without internet. A user who has already loaded today's plan should be able to see it, lock meals, and record interactions even when their connection drops. The architecture ensures this with three components: plan cache, event queue, and network state monitor.

| **Component** | **Implementation** | **Data persisted** | **Recovery behaviour** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Plan cache (TanStack Query + MMKV persister)** | TanStack Query's queryClient is configured with a MMKV-backed persister. When plan data is fetched successfully, it is written synchronously to MMKV. On next app open (online or offline), MMKV returns the cached plan instantly. | Today's plan (7-day plan cache for week view). Dish detail for previously viewed dishes. User profile. | Stale-while-revalidate: shows cached plan immediately, refetches in background when online. Offline banner shown via NetInfo.isConnected. |
| **Interaction event queue** | All interaction events (dish_accepted, dish_never, dish_not_today, lock, etc.) that fail to POST to /v1/events are serialised to MMKV event_queue key as a JSON array. | Array of pending REEvent objects: {event_type, dish_id, meal_slot, context, timestamp, retry_count} | On NetInfo connectionChange event (offline → online): flush queue. POST all queued events to /v1/events in order. Clear queue on success. Max 3 retries per event before logging to Sentry. |
| **Network state monitor** | @react-native-community/netinfo. Listens for connection state changes. Exposed via useNetworkStatus hook. | Connection type + isConnected boolean. Stored in Zustand network-store. | On offline: show offline banner (H-01 info-blue stripe). Disable actions that require network. On reconnect: flush event queue, refetch plan in background. |
| **Push notification handling** | OneSignal notification received offline: tap opens app, app reads from MMKV cache. Notification data (dish name, thumbnail) shown from notification payload itself (not from a network call). | Notification payload includes: dish_id, dish_name, dish_photo_url (CDN, not Supabase direct) | No network call needed to open notification and see breakfast suggestion. |

# **09  Timezone handling — IST / UTC rules**

| **Non-negotiable rule: **All timestamps stored in PostgreSQL as timestamptz (UTC). India is IST = UTC+5:30. The conversion must happen in the right place — mishandling this produces plans with the wrong date for users. |
| --- |

| **Rule** | **Implementation** | **Common mistake to avoid** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **All DB timestamps in UTC** | Every created_at, updated_at, plan_date column is timestamptz. Never timezone-naive timestamp. | Storing IST time as a timezone-naive timestamp — causes off-by-5:30 errors in all date queries. |
| **Plan date uses IST date** | When generating a plan for 'today', compute the IST date: new Date() + 5.5 hours = IST date. Use that date as plan_date. A plan generated at 11:30 PM UTC = 5:00 AM IST is for the NEXT day in IST. | Using UTC date as plan_date — users in India see yesterday's plan at 12:01 AM IST (6:30 PM UTC). |
| **Cron jobs scheduled in UTC** | Morning cron: 23:30 UTC = 05:00 AM IST. Supabase cron (pg_cron) uses UTC. | Scheduling cron at 05:00 UTC = 10:30 AM IST. Plan generation 5.5 hours too late. |
| **Notification time stored in IST** | user.notification_time stored as HH:MM in IST. When scheduling OneSignal, convert: UTC_time = IST_time - 5h30m. | Storing notification time in UTC — user sets 7:00 AM, receives at 12:30 PM IST. |
| **Client displays in device timezone** | All timestamps displayed to user use the device's local timezone (IST for Indian users). Use date-fns or Intl.DateTimeFormat with timezone awareness. | Displaying UTC timestamp directly — shows '1:30 AM' when user meant '7:00 AM'. |
| **'****Today****'**** calculation in Edge Functions** | const today = new Date(); today.setMinutes(today.getMinutes() + 330); // +5:30 hours for IST. Use today.toISOString().split('T')[0] for plan_date. | Using new Date().toISOString() without IST offset — off by a day for evening plan generation. |

