# **11  Scalability path**

| **Scale** | **Infrastructure** | **Cost/month** | **Key changes from previous tier** | **RE state** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **100 DAU (MVP launch)** | Supabase Free tier. Cloudinary free. OneSignal free. PostHog free. GitHub Actions free. | ₹0 | Initial architecture as described in this document. | classfirst_v1. Pure rule-based. |
| **500 DAU (MVP success)** | Supabase Free tier still sufficient. Monitor DB at 70% capacity. | ₹0 | No changes. Free tier handles comfortably. | classfirst_v2 (personal history learning active). |
| **2,000 DAU (Phase 0.5–1)** | Supabase Pro ($25/month). Connection pooler important at this scale. Cloudinary free sufficient. | ~₹2,000/month | Upgrade Supabase to Pro for connection pooling + 8GB DB + enhanced Edge Function limits. | classfirst_v2/v3. |
| **10,000 DAU (Phase 1.5–2)** | Supabase Pro + read replica for RE queries. Cloudinary Pro for CDN. EAS priority build queue. | ~₹8,000–15,000/month | Add read replica. Separate RE read queries to replica. Add Redis cache (Upstash free) for cohort_matrix (hot data). | cluster_v1 activated. |
| **50,000 DAU (Phase 3)** | Supabase Business or self-hosted. Dedicated RE service consideration. Multi-region possible. | ~₹40,000–80,000/month | Evaluate migrating RE to dedicated service. Feature store may benefit from Redis upgrade. | ltr_v1 if data sufficient. |
| **200,000+ DAU (Year 2+)** | Custom infrastructure. Kubernetes. Horizontal scaling of RE. Dedicated ML training pipeline. | Revenue-funded | Full architectural evolution per RE-DOC-05 Phase D recommendations. | ml_v1. |

